SIMPLE: displayed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Displayed
<hw>Dis*played"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Unfolded; expanded; exhibited conspicuously or
ostentatiously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>With wings expanded; -- said of a
bird of prey, esp. an eagle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>Set with lines of prominent type
interspersed, to catch the eye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Displayer</ent>⟦br⟧
